═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PRIORITY ORDER for wiring hooks
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Wire in this order — each unlocks more meaningful PRIME scores:

1. ND_NUM  (CONST)       — trivial, zero risk, immediately adds nodes
2. ND_RETURN             — every function gets a terminal node
3. ND_ADD/SUB/MUL        — arithmetic shows up in most functions
4. ND_VAR (LOAD)         — variable reads, very common
5. ND_ASSIGN (STORE)     — variable writes
6. ND_EQ/NE/LT/LE/GT/GE  — comparisons, needed for branch scoring
7. ND_IF / ND_WHILE      — branch labels, unlocks branch_count > 0
8. ND_FUNCALL            — call chain, unlocks call_count > 0
9. ND_DIV/MOD            — signed/unsigned correctness matters here
